        <span style="font-weight:700">3. Dynamics and Conversations</span><br>
        Dynamics are the conditions under which we want the user to complete the survey. Examples of dynamics include time i.e, a timed survey, limited characters for a response etc.,
        Choosing a dynamic depends on the goal of the project. Through Drapermeter, we are trying to see patterns in people's perception of creativity, hence the data collected through this survey should
        be numerical and ordinal. Likert Scale Questionnaires are the standard way of collecting ordinal data. Input for likert scale questionnaire can either be through radio buttons or sliders. In most of the popular
        survey applications radio buttons ae used for this kind of responses.
